            <title>[CASSANDRA-6481] Batchlog endpoint candidates should be picked randomly, not sorted by proximity</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6481</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Batchlog endpoint candidates should be picked randomly, not sorted by proximity. I&apos;ll be lazy and just copy-paste some lines from IRC:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;20:23:27&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; rbranson:	 is there an issue where batch logs tend to get written to a subset of the nodes?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;20:28:04&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; rbranson:	 I mean all the write batches are going thru 10% of the nodes&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;20:28:16&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; rbranson:	 it means writes won&apos;t scale linearly w/the cluster size&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attaching a trivial patch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
